Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.hashtable

Class FrequencyCounter<Key>

java.lang.Object
com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.BaseImmutableSymbolTable<Key,Integer>
com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.hashtable.FrequencyCounter<Key>
Type Parameters:
Key - the key type.
All Implemented Interfaces:
ImmutableSymbolTable<Key,Integer>
public class FrequencyCounter<Key> extends BaseImmutableSymbolTable<Key,Integer>
This class defines a specialized type of symbol table where the value corresponding to a key is the count of the number of times increment has been called for that key.

  • Method Details

    • get

      public Integer get(Key key)
      Retrieves the value associated with the given key from the symbol table. If the key is not present in the symbol table, the method returns a default value of 0.
      Parameters:
      key - the key whose associated value is to be returned.
      Returns:
      the value associated with the specified key, or 0 if the key is not present.

    • relativeFrequency

      public double relativeFrequency(Key key)
      Calculates the relative frequency of a specified key. The relative frequency is determined by dividing the number of occurrences of the key by the total number of increments across all keys.
      Parameters:
      key - the key whose relative frequency is to be calculated.
      Returns:
      the relative frequency of the specified key as a double.

    • relativeFrequencyAsPercentage

      public double relativeFrequencyAsPercentage(Key key)
      Calculates the relative frequency of a specified key as a percentage. The relative frequency is determined by multiplying the result of the method relativeFrequency(Key) by 100.
      Parameters:
      key - the key whose relative frequency as a percentage is to be calculated.
      Returns:
      the relative frequency of the specified key as a percentage, represented as a double.

    • increment

      public void increment(Key s)
      Increments the frequency count of the specified key in the symbol table. If the key does not exist in the table, it initializes its count to 1. Additionally, increments the total frequency count across all keys.
      Parameters:
      s - the key whose frequency count is to be incremented
